thread.title: Sounders clinch playoff spot with 3-1 win against Real Salt Lake

Mark Moschetti

title: Sounders clinch playoff spot with 3-1 win against Real Salt Lake
text:
October 25, 2015 Sounders clinch playoff spot with 3-1 win against Real Salt Lake Sounders forward Clint Dempsey, left, acknowledges the crowd Sunday after scoring his second goal against Real Salt Lake in a 3-1 win for Seattle at CenturyLink Field. The Sounders will play host to the Los Angeles Galaxy in a playoff elimination game later this week. Dean J. Koepfler The News Tribune i Order Reprint of this Story SEATTLE 
Clint Dempsey scored two goals and assisted on another, all in the first 20 minutes of the game, as the Seattle Sounders beat Real Salt Lake, 3-1, to wrap up an MLS playoff berth Sunday. 
The Sounders (15-13-6, 51 points) ended the regular season on an eight-game unbeaten streak (4-0-4). They have made the playoffs in all seven years of their existence. 
With Sundayâ€™s other results, the Sounders are the No. 4 seed in the Western Conference. They will play host to No. 5 seed and defending MLS Cup champion Los Angeles in a knockout game on Wednesday. 
Dempsey put the Sounders on the board in the fifth minute when he met a cross from Obafemi Martins at the top right corner of the 6-yard box and sent it into the net while falling to the turf. It was his ninth goal of the year. 
Marco Pappa scored in the 10th minute off of a cross from Dempsey. In the 20th Dempsey made it 3-0 when he buried the rebound of a hard shot by Martins. Luis Gill scored in the 77th minute for Salt Lake (11-15-8, 41 points), which missed the playoffs after seven consecutive appearances. Related content
